radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated appendicitis with a 1.6 cm fluid-filled appendix demonstrating mucosal hyperemia, two appendicoliths measuring up to 1.3 cm, diverticulosis of the sigmoid colon, a 1.8 cm simple cyst in the upper pole of the left kidney, mild degenerative changes in the lumbar spine, and a 1.9 x 0.9 cm lucent lesion in L4. No other focal lesions or abnormalities in the liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenals, urinary bladder, or distal ureters. No free air or drainable fluid collections.
